# 2D Technical Drawing Annotation — AutoCAD & VectorWorks

Dimension, tolerance, and part reference annotation on 2D CAD drawings for AI component recognition.

## Overview
Technical drawings produced in AutoCAD Mechanical and VectorWorks are annotated with structured labels covering dimensions, tolerances, material specifications, and part identifiers. Output supports AI-driven component classification pipelines.

## Tools Used
- AutoCAD Mechanical
- VectorWorks
- LibreCAD / QCAD CE

## Annotation Fields
| Field | Example | Description |
|-------|---------|-------------|
| `PART` | `BRK-04` | Part identifier |
| `TOL` | `±0.05mm` | Manufacturing tolerance |
| `MAT` | `STEEL` | Material specification |
| `DIM` | `75mm` | Key dimension |

## Sample Annotation Block
```
PART: BRK-04
DIM:  75mm × 40mm
TOL:  ±0.05
MAT:  MILD STEEL
REV:  v3
```

